## 8. Backend Blueprint Spec: `art_store_blueprint.py`

Clone `repsetta_blueprint.py` structure (no templates, no SQLite table, pure
in-memory seed + JWT signing).

```
art_store_bp = Blueprint("art_store", __name__, url_prefix="/art-store")

Endpoints:
  POST /art-store/login
    Body: { email, password }  (any values accepted)
    Returns: { token: <JWT signed with server SECRET_KEY, exp 1h, sub: email> }

  GET /art-store/prints
    Returns: PRINTS seed list (12 items, Picsum URLs)
    No auth required

  POST /art-store/checkout
    Header: Authorization: Bearer <token>
    Body: { items: [{printId, size, qty, price}], total }
    Returns: { orderId: "MW-<uuid4 short>", status: "confirmed",
               estimatedShipping: "3-5 business days", total }
```

JWT signing: use the existing `SECRET_KEY = os.getenv("SECRET_KEY", "dev-secret")`
pattern (already used by server.py core auth). No new env var needed.

Seed data: 12 prints using `https://picsum.photos/seed/<slug>/800/1000` URLs.
Each print has: id, slug, title, artist (fictional), price (base for 8x10),
edition (limited/open), editionSize (25 for limited), sizes with prices, tags.

